text: Martin Sjögren (born 27 April 1977) is a Swedish football coach. He became the coach of the Norway women's national football team in 2016. He won the Damallsvenskan title with Linköpings FC in 2016, then agreed to take the Norway national team job. ==References== ==Other websites== * Profile at Linköpings FC Category:1977 births Category:Living people Category:Swedish footballers Category:Swedish football managers
